```
// BAD: Directly concatenating user input into an SQL string – vulnerable to SQL Injection
String userId = request.getParameter("id");                 // attacker can send: id=5 OR 1=1
String sql = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE user_id = '" + userId + "'";
Statement stmt = connection.createStatement();
ResultSet rs = stmt.executeQuery(sql);                      // executes attacker's arbitrary SQL
```

***

```
// GOOD: Use parameterized queries to keep code and data separate – removes SQL Injection vector
String userId = request.getParameter("id");                 // untrusted input
String sql = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE user_id = ?";       // ? placeholder prevents injection
PreparedStatement ps = connection.prepareStatement(sql);
ps.setString(1, userId);                                    // driver safely escapes the value
ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery();                           // safe execution
```

